# Concrete projection operator for the TRAE rate theorem

This file defines the concrete projection operator
    `T h := О _{QМ„} вҲҳ E[В· | Пғ(Z)]`
used in the simplified rate theorem of
`doc/basic_concepts/po/estimation/trae_inverse_problems.tex` (lines 250вҖ“384).

## Design

`Setup.lean` keeps `Hbar`, `Qbar` as plain function sets without
Hilbert structure, since the mixed-bias proof only needs algebraic linearity.
The rate theorem requires an LВІ realization: closed subspaces
`Hbar_L2`, `Qbar_L2 : Submodule в„қ (Lp в„қ 2 Ој)` of the *ambient* `Lp в„қ 2 Ој`,
together with embeddings of function-level members.  We choose the ambient
`Lp в„қ 2 Ој` (rather than pushforward `Lp в„қ 2 (Ој.map X)`) so the conditional
expectation `condExpL2` can be applied directly without pushforward
identifications.

The Пғ-algebra "generated by `Z`" is encoded as
`m_Z := MeasurableSpace.comap S.zOf S.instрқ’ө вҲҳ (... lifted along W)` вҖ”
concretely `MeasurableSpace.comap (zOf вҲҳ W) instрқ’ө`, with a hypothesis
`m_Z_le : m_Z вүӨ mвӮҖ`.

The operator `T h` is then:
1.  lift `h вҲҳ X : О© вҶ’ в„қ` into `Lp в„қ 2 Ој` (via a `MemLp` hypothesis on
    `OperatorSystem`);
2.  apply `MeasureTheory.condExpL2 в„қ в„қ m_Z_le` (a continuous linear map into
    the Пғ(Z)-measurable subspace);
3.  project onto `Qbar_L2` via `Submodule.orthogonalProjectionFn`.

The single population identity exported here, `T_inner_eq_integral`, is what
the rate theorem consumes.  Its proof combines `condExpL2` self-adjointness
with the orthogonality characterization of `Qbar_L2`-projection; it is fully
proved (no sorries).

The adjoint `T*` and the self-adjoint composite `TвҖ T` are bundled in
`Operator/Adjoint.lean`; this file focuses on the unbundled projection operator
and the population identity needed by the DR rate argument.
-/

import Causalean.Estimation.NPIV.Setup
import Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Function.ConditionalExpectation.CondexpL2
import Mathlib.Analysis.InnerProductSpace.Projection.Basic

/-!
Extends the inverse-problem system with population operators for NPIV
estimation. The module defines the operator interface connecting structural
functions, instruments, and conditional-moment equations.
-/

namespace Causalean
namespace Estimation
namespace NPIV

open MeasureTheory
open scoped InnerProductSpace

/-! ## Operator-system extension of `InverseProblemSystem` -/

/-- An **operator system**: an `InverseProblemSystem` enriched with the LВІ
data needed to define the concrete projection operator
`T = О _{QМ„} вҲҳ E[В· | Пғ(Z)]`.

The closed subspaces `Hbar_L2`, `Qbar_L2 : Submodule в„қ (Lp в„қ 2 Ој)` realize
the candidate sets inside the *ambient* `Lp в„қ 2 Ој`.  We additionally carry:

* the Пғ-algebra `m_Z` generated by `Z = zOf вҲҳ W` and a proof it is coarser
  than `mвӮҖ`, so that `condExpL2 в„қ в„қ m_Z_le` is well-typed;
* `MemLp` witnesses for `h вҲҳ X` (`h вҲҲ Hbar`) and `q вҲҳ Z` (`q вҲҲ Qbar`),
  together with coherence: their LВІ classes lie in `Hbar_L2` / `Qbar_L2`;
* `[Fact (Ој.IsFiniteMeasure)]`-style finiteness of `Ој` (needed by some
  conditional-expectation identities).
-/
structure OperatorSystem
    (О© : Type*) [mвӮҖ : MeasurableSpace О©] (Ој : Measure О©)
    extends InverseProblemSystem О© Ој where
  /-- The Пғ-algebra generated by `Z = zOf вҲҳ W : О© вҶ’ рқ’ө`. -/
  m_Z : MeasurableSpace О©
  /-- `m_Z` is coarser than `mвӮҖ`. -/
  m_Z_le : m_Z вүӨ mвӮҖ
  /-- (Optional consistency:) `m_Z = comap (zOf вҲҳ W) instрқ’ө`.  This pins the
  Пғ-algebra to the one generated by `Z`. -/
  m_Z_eq : m_Z =
    @MeasurableSpace.comap О© рқ’ө (fun Пү => zOf (W Пү)) instрқ’ө
  /-- `Ој` is finite (sufficient for the conditional-expectation identities
  used in the rate proof). -/
  isFiniteMeasure : IsFiniteMeasure Ој
  /-- LВІ realization of `Hbar`: a closed submodule of the ambient `Lp в„қ 2 Ој`. -/
  Hbar_L2 : Submodule в„қ (Lp в„қ 2 Ој)
  /-- LВІ realization of `Qbar`. -/
  Qbar_L2 : Submodule в„қ (Lp в„қ 2 Ој)
  /-- `Qbar_L2` admits an orthogonal projection (in particular, is closed). -/
  Qbar_L2_hasProj : Qbar_L2.HasOrthogonalProjection
  /-- Embedding witness: for every `h вҲҲ Hbar`, the function
  `Пү вҶҰ h (X Пү) = h (xOf (W Пү))` is square-integrable. -/
  toHbarL2 : вҲҖ h вҲҲ Hbar, MemLp (fun Пү => h (xOf (W Пү))) 2 Ој
  /-- Embedding witness: for every `q вҲҲ Qbar`, the function
  `Пү вҶҰ q (Z Пү) = q (zOf (W Пү))` is square-integrable. -/
  toQbarL2 : вҲҖ q вҲҲ Qbar, MemLp (fun Пү => q (zOf (W Пү))) 2 Ој
  /-- Coherence: the `Lp` class of `h вҲҳ X` lies in the closed subspace
  `Hbar_L2`. -/
  hbar_mem_L2 :
    вҲҖ h (hh : h вҲҲ Hbar), (toHbarL2 h hh).toLp _ вҲҲ Hbar_L2
  /-- Coherence: the `Lp` class of `q вҲҳ Z` lies in `Qbar_L2`. -/
  qbar_mem_L2 :
    вҲҖ q (hq : q вҲҲ Qbar), (toQbarL2 q hq).toLp _ вҲҲ Qbar_L2

namespace OperatorSystem

variable {О© : Type*} [MeasurableSpace О©] {Ој : Measure О©}

/-- Lift `h вҲҲ Hbar` to its LВІ class
`(h вҲҳ X)_{Lp} вҲҲ Lp в„қ 2 Ој`.  This is just a name. -/
noncomputable def hL2 (S : OperatorSystem О© Ој) {h : S.рқ’і вҶ’ в„қ}
    (hh : h вҲҲ S.Hbar) : Lp в„қ 2 Ој :=
  (S.toHbarL2 h hh).toLp _

/-- Lift `q вҲҲ Qbar` to its LВІ class
`(q вҲҳ Z)_{Lp} вҲҲ Lp в„қ 2 Ој`. -/
noncomputable def qL2 (S : OperatorSystem О© Ој) {q : S.рқ’ө вҶ’ в„қ}
    (hq : q вҲҲ S.Qbar) : Lp в„қ 2 Ој :=
  (S.toQbarL2 q hq).toLp _

/-! ## The projection operator `T`

We define `T` on the ambient `Lp в„қ 2 Ој` (so its action on `Hbar`-side
elements is `T (S.hL2 hh)`).  Composition order:
`T = orthogonalProjectionFn Qbar_L2 вҲҳ (condExpL2 в„қ в„қ m_Z_le)`. -/

/-- The conditional-expectation step `E[В· | Пғ(Z)]`, viewed as a self-map
of `Lp в„қ 2 Ој` (via the canonical inclusion of the Пғ(Z)-measurable
subspace).

This is the composition
`Lp 2 Ој вҶ’L[в„қ] lpMeas в„қ в„қ m_Z 2 Ој вҶ’ Lp 2 Ој`
where the second arrow is the structural inclusion (each `lpMeas` element
*is* an `Lp` element). -/
noncomputable def condExpStep (S : OperatorSystem О© Ој) :
    Lp в„қ 2 Ој вҶ’ Lp в„қ 2 Ој :=
  haveI := S.isFiniteMeasure
  fun f => (MeasureTheory.condExpL2 в„қ в„қ S.m_Z_le f : Lp в„қ 2 Ој)

/-- The concrete projection operator
`T = О _{QМ„} вҲҳ E[В· | Пғ(Z)]`.

Acts on the ambient `Lp в„қ 2 Ој`; the rate theorem applies it to
`S.hL2 hh - S.hL2 hh' = (S.hL2 hh) - (S.hL2 hh')`. -/
noncomputable def T (S : OperatorSystem О© Ој) (f : Lp в„қ 2 Ој) : Lp в„қ 2 Ој :=
  haveI := S.Qbar_L2_hasProj
  S.Qbar_L2.orthogonalProjectionFn (S.condExpStep f)

/-! ## Linearity helpers for `T`

`T = О _{QМ„} вҲҳ condExpL2` is a composition of two в„қ-linear maps:

* `condExpL2 в„қ в„қ S.m_Z_le : Lp 2 Ој вҶ’L[в„қ] (lpMeas в„қ в„қ S.m_Z 2 Ој)`, then
  embedded into `Lp 2 Ој` (linear by definition of `condExpStep`).
* `Submodule.orthogonalProjectionFn` agrees with the bundled
  `Submodule.orthogonalProjection : E вҶ’L[в„қ] K` followed by the
  subtype embedding (`Submodule.orthogonalProjectionFn_eq`), so it is
  в„қ-linear too.

We expose the two basic linearity lemmas the rate proof consumes
(`T_add`, `T_sub`); a `LinearMap` form is not needed at this stage. -/

/-- `condExpStep` distributes over subtraction (linearity of
`condExpL2`). -/
lemma condExpStep_sub (S : OperatorSystem О© Ој) (f g : Lp в„қ 2 Ој) :
    S.condExpStep (f - g) = S.condExpStep f - S.condExpStep g := by
  haveI := S.isFiniteMeasure
  unfold condExpStep
  simp [map_sub]

/-- `T` distributes over subtraction. -/
lemma T_sub (S : OperatorSystem О© Ој) (f g : Lp в„қ 2 Ој) :
    S.T (f - g) = S.T f - S.T g := by
  haveI := S.Qbar_L2_hasProj
  unfold T
  rw [S.condExpStep_sub]
  -- Reduce `orthogonalProjectionFn (a - b)` to
  -- `orthogonalProjectionFn a - orthogonalProjectionFn b` via the
  -- rfl-equality `orthogonalProjectionFn = ((orthogonalProjection В·) : _)`
  -- and `map_sub` on the bundled CLM `orthogonalProjection`.
  change ((S.Qbar_L2.orthogonalProjection (S.condExpStep f - S.condExpStep g)) : Lp в„қ 2 Ој)
        = ((S.Qbar_L2.orthogonalProjection (S.condExpStep f)) : Lp в„қ 2 Ој)
            - ((S.Qbar_L2.orthogonalProjection (S.condExpStep g)) : Lp в„қ 2 Ој)
  rw [map_sub]
  rfl

/-- `T` distributes over addition (companion to `T_sub`). -/
lemma T_add (S : OperatorSystem О© Ој) (f g : Lp в„қ 2 Ој) :
    S.T (f + g) = S.T f + S.T g := by
  haveI := S.Qbar_L2_hasProj
  haveI := S.isFiniteMeasure
  unfold T condExpStep
  change ((S.Qbar_L2.orthogonalProjection
            ((MeasureTheory.condExpL2 в„қ в„қ S.m_Z_le (f + g) : Lp в„қ 2 Ој))) : Lp в„қ 2 Ој)
        = ((S.Qbar_L2.orthogonalProjection
            ((MeasureTheory.condExpL2 в„қ в„қ S.m_Z_le f : Lp в„қ 2 Ој))) : Lp в„қ 2 Ој)
          + ((S.Qbar_L2.orthogonalProjection
            ((MeasureTheory.condExpL2 в„қ в„қ S.m_Z_le g : Lp в„қ 2 Ој))) : Lp в„қ 2 Ој)
  simp [map_add]

/-! ## Population identity

The rate theorem (`trae_inverse_problems.tex` lines 250вҖ“384) needs exactly
one population identity for `T`:

    вҹЁT (h - h'), fвҹ©_{LВІ(Ој)}
      = вҲ« Пү, (h (X Пү) - h' (X Пү)) В· f (Z Пү) вҲӮОј

for `h, h' вҲҲ Hbar` and `f вҲҲ Qbar`.  Sketch of proof:

1.  By `Submodule.orthogonalProjectionFn_inner_eq_zero` applied to
    `S.Qbar_L2` and `S.qL2 hf вҲҲ S.Qbar_L2`, the projection step is
    invisible in the inner product:
        вҹЁT u, qL2 hfвҹ© = вҹЁcondExpStep u, qL2 hfвҹ©.

2.  By `MeasureTheory.inner_condExpL2_left_eq_right` (self-adjointness of
    `condExpL2`) and the fact that `qL2 hf` is already
    Пғ(Z)-measurable (so `condExpL2 (qL2 hf) = qL2 hf`), we get
        вҹЁcondExpStep u, qL2 hfвҹ© = вҹЁu, qL2 hfвҹ©.

3.  Unwinding `Lp` inner products to integrals (`L2.inner_def`) yields
    the right-hand side.

Step 2 needs `S.qL2 hf` to actually live in the Пғ(Z)-measurable subspace;
that is the content of `qbar_aestrongly_measurable_mZ` below (proven from
`m_Z_eq` and `meas_of_Qbar`, no extra hypothesis required). -/

/-- Hypothesis used by `T_inner_eq_integral`: `q вҲҳ Z` is `m_Z`-strongly
measurable (a.e.).  Derivable from `m_Z_eq` and `meas_of_Qbar`; see
`qbar_aestrongly_measurable_mZ` below.  Kept as a `def` so existing call
sites (which take it as a separate hypothesis) continue to compile. -/
def QbarAEMeasurableMZ (S : OperatorSystem О© Ој) : Prop :=
  вҲҖ q, q вҲҲ S.Qbar вҶ’
    AEStronglyMeasurable[S.m_Z] (fun Пү => q (S.zOf (S.W Пү))) Ој

/-- `q вҲҳ zOf вҲҳ W` is `m_Z`-strongly measurable for every `q вҲҲ Qbar`.
Direct consequence of `m_Z_eq : m_Z = comap (zOf вҲҳ W) instрқ’ө` and
`meas_of_Qbar`: the canonical map `(zOf вҲҳ W) : О© вҶ’ рқ’ө` is measurable from
`comap (zOf вҲҳ W) instрқ’ө` to `instрқ’ө` (`comap_measurable`), so its
composition with the `instрқ’ө`-measurable `q : рқ’ө вҶ’ в„қ` is
`m_Z`-measurable, hence `m_Z`-strongly measurable into в„қ. -/
lemma qbar_aestrongly_measurable_mZ (S : OperatorSystem О© Ој) :
    S.QbarAEMeasurableMZ := by
  intro q hq
  have hZ : @Measurable О© S.рқ’ө S.m_Z S.instрқ’ө (fun Пү => S.zOf (S.W Пү)) := by
    rw [S.m_Z_eq]
    exact comap_measurable _
  have hq_meas : @Measurable S.рқ’ө в„қ S.instрқ’ө _ q := S.meas_of_Qbar q hq
  have h_meas :
      @Measurable О© в„қ S.m_Z _ (fun Пү => q (S.zOf (S.W Пү))) :=
    @Measurable.comp О© S.рқ’ө в„қ S.m_Z S.instрқ’ө _ q
      (fun Пү => S.zOf (S.W Пү)) hq_meas hZ
  exact h_meas.aestronglyMeasurable

/-- **Population identity for `T`.**  For `h, h' вҲҲ Hbar` and `f вҲҲ Qbar`,

    вҹЁT (hL2 hh - hL2 hh'), qL2 hfвҹ©_{LВІ(Ој)}
      = вҲ« Пү, (h (X Пү) - h' (X Пү)) В· f (Z Пү) вҲӮОј.

This is the only identity the simplified TRAE rate proof requires from `T`.
The proof composes:

* invisibility of `О _{QМ„}` against a `QМ„`-element
  (`Submodule.orthogonalProjectionFn_inner_eq_zero` on the residual);
* self-adjointness of `condExpL2` and idempotence on Пғ(Z)-measurable
  LВІ classes (uses `qbar_meas_mZ`);
* unwinding `Lp` inner products to Bochner integrals.
-/
theorem T_inner_eq_integral
    (S : OperatorSystem О© Ој)
    {h h' : S.рқ’і вҶ’ в„қ} (hh : h вҲҲ S.Hbar) (hh' : h' вҲҲ S.Hbar)
    {f : S.рқ’ө вҶ’ в„қ} (hf : f вҲҲ S.Qbar) :
    inner в„қ (S.T (S.hL2 hh - S.hL2 hh')) (S.qL2 hf)
      = вҲ« Пү, (h (S.xOf (S.W Пү)) - h' (S.xOf (S.W Пү))) *
              f (S.zOf (S.W Пү)) вҲӮОј := by
  haveI := S.isFiniteMeasure
  haveI := S.Qbar_L2_hasProj
  let u : Lp в„қ 2 Ој := S.hL2 hh - S.hL2 hh'
  have hq_mem : S.qL2 hf вҲҲ S.Qbar_L2 := S.qbar_mem_L2 f hf
  have h_proj :
      inner в„қ (S.T u) (S.qL2 hf) =
        inner в„қ (S.condExpStep u) (S.qL2 hf) := by
    have h_zero :
        inner в„қ (S.condExpStep u - S.Qbar_L2.orthogonalProjectionFn (S.condExpStep u))
          (S.qL2 hf) = 0 :=
      S.Qbar_L2.orthogonalProjectionFn_inner_eq_zero (S.condExpStep u) (S.qL2 hf) hq_mem
    have h_eq :
        inner в„қ (S.condExpStep u) (S.qL2 hf) =
          inner в„қ (S.Qbar_L2.orthogonalProjectionFn (S.condExpStep u)) (S.qL2 hf) := by
      rw [inner_sub_left] at h_zero
      exact sub_eq_zero.mp h_zero
    simpa [OperatorSystem.T] using h_eq.symm
  have hq_meas :
      AEStronglyMeasurable[S.m_Z] (S.qL2 hf : О© вҶ’ в„қ) Ој :=
    (S.qbar_aestrongly_measurable_mZ f hf).congr (S.toQbarL2 f hf).coeFn_toLp.symm
  have h_cond :
      inner в„қ (S.condExpStep u) (S.qL2 hf) =
        inner в„қ u (S.qL2 hf) := by
    simpa [OperatorSystem.condExpStep] using
      (MeasureTheory.inner_condExpL2_eq_inner_fun (E := в„қ) (рқ•ң := в„қ)
        S.m_Z_le u (S.qL2 hf) hq_meas)
  have h_inner :
      inner в„қ u (S.qL2 hf) =
        вҲ« Пү, (h (S.xOf (S.W Пү)) - h' (S.xOf (S.W Пү))) *
              f (S.zOf (S.W Пү)) вҲӮОј := by
    rw [MeasureTheory.L2.inner_def]
    refine integral_congr_ae ?_
    filter_upwards [Lp.coeFn_sub (S.hL2 hh) (S.hL2 hh'),
      (S.toHbarL2 h hh).coeFn_toLp, (S.toHbarL2 h' hh').coeFn_toLp,
      (S.toQbarL2 f hf).coeFn_toLp] with Пү hu hhПү hh'Пү hfПү
    calc
      вҹӘu Пү, (S.qL2 hf) Пүвҹ«_в„қ
          = вҹӘ(S.hL2 hh) Пү - (S.hL2 hh') Пү, (S.qL2 hf) Пүвҹ«_в„қ := by
            have huПү : u Пү = (S.hL2 hh) Пү - (S.hL2 hh') Пү := by
              simpa [u, Pi.sub_apply] using hu
            rw [huПү]
      _ = вҹӘh (S.xOf (S.W Пү)) - h' (S.xOf (S.W Пү)),
            f (S.zOf (S.W Пү))вҹ«_в„қ := by
            simp [OperatorSystem.hL2, OperatorSystem.qL2, hhПү, hh'Пү, hfПү]
      _ = (h (S.xOf (S.W Пү)) - h' (S.xOf (S.W Пү))) *
            f (S.zOf (S.W Пү)) := by
            change f (S.zOf (S.W Пү)) *
                (h (S.xOf (S.W Пү)) - h' (S.xOf (S.W Пү))) =
              (h (S.xOf (S.W Пү)) - h' (S.xOf (S.W Пү))) *
                f (S.zOf (S.W Пү))
            ring
  calc
    inner в„қ (S.T (S.hL2 hh - S.hL2 hh')) (S.qL2 hf)
        = inner в„қ (S.T u) (S.qL2 hf) := by simp [u]
    _ = inner в„қ (S.condExpStep u) (S.qL2 hf) := h_proj
    _ = inner в„қ u (S.qL2 hf) := h_cond
    _ = вҲ« Пү, (h (S.xOf (S.W Пү)) - h' (S.xOf (S.W Пү))) *
              f (S.zOf (S.W Пү)) вҲӮОј := h_inner

/-! ## Norm helpers

The simplified rate theorem packages two seminorms:

* the **strong norm** `вҖ–h - h'вҖ–_{strong} := вҖ–hL2 hh - hL2 hh'вҖ–_{LВІ(Ој)}`,
  i.e. the ambient `Lp` norm of the lifted residual;
* the **weak norm** `вҖ–h - h'вҖ–_{weak} := вҖ–T (hL2 hh - hL2 hh')вҖ–_{LВІ(Ој)}`,
  i.e. the `Lp` norm after projection.

We expose them on the lifted `Lp в„қ 2 Ој` argument (no ambient `MemLp`
witness juggling). -/

/-- Strong (`LВІ`) norm of an LВІ element. -/
noncomputable def strongNorm (_S : OperatorSystem О© Ој) (f : Lp в„қ 2 Ој) : в„қ :=
  вҖ–fвҖ–

/-- Weak norm associated to `T`: `вҖ–T fвҖ–_{LВІ(Ој)}`. -/
noncomputable def weakNorm (S : OperatorSystem О© Ој) (f : Lp в„қ 2 Ој) : в„қ :=
  вҖ–S.T fвҖ–

/-- The projected conditional-expectation norm is bounded by the ambient
`LВІ` norm. -/
lemma weakNorm_le_strongNorm (S : OperatorSystem О© Ој) (f : Lp в„қ 2 Ој) :
    S.weakNorm f вүӨ S.strongNorm f := by
  haveI := S.isFiniteMeasure
  haveI := S.Qbar_L2_hasProj
  calc
    S.weakNorm f = вҖ–S.Qbar_L2.starProjection (S.condExpStep f)вҖ– := by
      rw [weakNorm, T]
      change вҖ–S.Qbar_L2.orthogonalProjectionFn (S.condExpStep f)вҖ– =
        вҖ–S.Qbar_L2.starProjection (S.condExpStep f)вҖ–
      rw [Submodule.orthogonalProjectionFn_eq, вҶҗ Submodule.starProjection_apply]
    _ вүӨ вҖ–S.condExpStep fвҖ– := S.Qbar_L2.norm_starProjection_apply_le (S.condExpStep f)
    _ вүӨ вҖ–fвҖ– := by
      simpa [condExpStep] using
        (MeasureTheory.norm_condExpL2_coe_le (E := в„қ) (рқ•ң := в„қ) S.m_Z_le f)
    _ = S.strongNorm f := by
      rw [strongNorm]

/-- Squared strong norm of a lifted `Hbar` member, unfolded as the integral
of the squared representative. -/
lemma strongNorm_sq_hL2_eq_integral
    (S : OperatorSystem О© Ој) {h : S.рқ’і вҶ’ в„қ} (hh : h вҲҲ S.Hbar) :
    (S.strongNorm (S.hL2 hh)) ^ 2 = вҲ« Пү, (h (S.xOf (S.W Пү))) ^ 2 вҲӮОј := by
  calc
    (S.strongNorm (S.hL2 hh)) ^ 2 = inner в„қ (S.hL2 hh) (S.hL2 hh) := by
      rw [OperatorSystem.strongNorm, real_inner_self_eq_norm_sq]
    _ = вҲ« Пү, вҹӘ(S.hL2 hh) Пү, (S.hL2 hh) Пүвҹ«_в„қ вҲӮОј := by
      rw [MeasureTheory.L2.inner_def]
    _ = вҲ« Пү, (h (S.xOf (S.W Пү))) ^ 2 вҲӮОј := by
      refine integral_congr_ae ?_
      filter_upwards [(S.toHbarL2 h hh).coeFn_toLp] with Пү hПү
      simp [OperatorSystem.hL2, hПү, pow_two]

end OperatorSystem

end NPIV
end Estimation
end Causalean
